ting societies: Canada’s far north. Based on his experiences travelling with First Nations Elders in remote communities across the Northwest Territories, Yukon, and Nunavut, this vivid narrative combines accounts of daily life, unpublished archival records, First Nations' stories and Traditional Knowledge with personal observation to illuminate the northern wilderness, its people, and the complex relationships that exist among them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEcotourismzCanada, Northern. 0aHuntingzCanada, Northern. 0aIndigenous peopleszCanada, NorthernxSocial life and customs. 7aTravel / Canada / Territories & Nunavut (NT, NU, YT).2bisacsh  aTravel Literature / The North / Indigenous Culture.1 aCarlucci, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311127380808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016z978311127630440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212146940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772121469423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772121469/original  a978-3-11-127380-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-127630-4  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles